filename: Emancipation- the past and the future (20186657008).jpg
author: ["Library Company of Philadelphia"]
description: ["English:", "Emancipation print from 1863 depicting a series of scenes contrasting African American life before and after slavery. Central scene portrays the interior of a freedman's home where several generations of the family socialize around a \"Union\" stove as the mother cooks. Below this scene is a vignette depicting Father Time holding a baby angel who has the year 1863 above his head and who frees the shackles of a kneeling male slave before him. Above the central scene is a depiction of Thomas Crawford's statue of freedom as well as the hell hound Cerberus fleeing Liberty. Scenes to the right display the horrors of slavery including the flogging, branding, selling, and capturing of slaves. Scenes to the left display the forthcoming results of freedom including the exterior of a freedman's cottage, African American children attending public school, and African Americans receiving payment for their work.  (10)1540.F", "Link to record on ImPAC, the Library Company\u2019s digital collections catalog:", "http://lcpdams.librarycompany.org:8881/R/-?func=dbin-jump-full&object_id=130265&silo_library=GEN01"]

author: ["Jebulon"]
description: ["English:", "Statue of the emperor Augustus (29BC - AD 14). Bronze. Found in the Aegean sea between the islands of Euboea and Agios Efstratios. The emperor is depicted in mature age, mounting a horse. He wears a tunica decorated with a meander pattern. Iconographic features of the Prima Porta gesture of official greeting. The hilt of his sword can be seen below the left hand, in which he held the horse's reigns. On the bezel of his finger-ring a staff of divination (lituus) is engraved, symbolizing the supreme religious office of Pontifex Maximus, assumed by Augustus in 12 BC. 12-10 BC", filename: Simon Bening (Flemish - Villagers on Their Way to Church - Google Art Project.jpg
artist: ["Simon Bening", "(circa 1483/1484\u20131561)", "Alternative names", "Simon Bering; Sim\u00e3o Bening; Simon Benning; Simon Beninc; Simon Benig", "Description", "Southern Netherlandish painter and", "manuscript illuminator", "Date of birth/death", "circa 1483-1484", "6 November 1561", "Location of birth/death", "Ghent", "Bruges", "Work location", "Ghent", ",", "Bruges", "(1508-1561)", "Authority control", ":", "Q928015", "VIAF", ":", "32139591", "ISNI", ":", "0000 0000 8342 7069", "ULAN", ":", "500115179", "LCCN", ":", "n87813931", "WGA", ":", "BENING, Simon", "WorldCat", "artist QS:P170,Q928015", "Details of artist on Google Art Project"]
title: ["Villagers on Their Way to Church"]
description:
["Simon Bening 
Flemish, probably Bruges, about 1550 
Tempera colors and gold paint on parchment 
2 3/16 x 3 3/4 in. 
MS. 50, RECTO", "As the local parish church prepares for services, villagers and rural peasants make their way down the path. In the distance, fields, gently rolling hills, buildings, and groves of trees give shape to the landscape. The candlelit procession inside the church, as well as the candles held by the approaching villagers, suggest the celebration of Candlemas, a church holiday observed the second of February.", "An earlier owner probably cut the miniature from the lower border of the calendar of a book of hours. Despite its small size, Bening's landscape achieves a monumentality associated with larger contemporary panel paintings, where the genre of landscape painting was developing along similar lines."]
medium: ["\nTempera colors and gold paint on parchment"]

filename: Tent revival during the Second Great Awakening.jpg
author: ["\nKelloggs & Comstock"]
description: ["English:", "Tent revivals were a hallmark of the Second Great Awakening. 1849 lithograph, Harry T. Peters \"America on Stone\" Lithography Collection. Colored print of a man preaching to a large group of men and women at Hartford, Connecticut, seated separately by gender on benches. In the background and on the side are tents with women seated in their openings. Eight men are seated on the platform behind the preacher. The tents are labeled with initials with the exception of one that says \"4St\". Two verses from the Bible appear below the image on each side of the title. (Smithsonian)", "Image: 8 x 12 in.; 20.32 x 30.48 cm", "ID number: DL*60.2964", "Negative number: 2003-24830"]

filename: Our Lady of the Gate of Dawn Vilnius (5987797374).jpg
author: ["FaceMePLS", "from The Hague, The Netherlands"]
description: ["Our Lady of the Gate of Dawn (Lithuanian: Au\u0161ros Vart\u0173 Dievo Motina, Polish: Matka Boska Ostrobramska, Belarusian: \u041c\u0430\u0446\u0456 \u0411\u043e\u0436\u0430\u044f \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0431\u0440\u0430\u043c\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f) is the prominent painting of the Blessed Virgin Mary venerated by the faithful in the Chapel of the Gate of Dawn. The Renaissance painting, completed possibly in the first half of the 17th century, is an unusual portrayal of Madonna as she is depicted without infant Jesus. The artwork soon became known as miraculous and inspired a following. A dedicated chapel was built in 1671 by the Discalced Carmelites. At the same time, possibly borrowing from the Eastern Orthodox tradition, the painting was covered in expensive and elaborate silver and gold clothes leaving only the face and hands visible. \nBron: Wikipedia", "Het hangt in een hele kleine ruimte en is niet alleen binnen te bewonderen (alleen via een lange steile trap te bereiken), maar ook vanaf de straat eronder, zie daarvoor de eerdere foto van de kapel. Als je slecht ter been bent, kun je op dagen dat het mooi weer is het icoon ook door het openstaande raam vanaf de straat zien, niet en detail, maar toch. De hele dag door bidden er binnen mensen, inwoners van Vilnius, veel nonnen en ook toeristen. Beneden op straat staan vaak (oudere) vrouwen uit Vilnius hun rozenkrans te bidden."]
source: ["'Our Lady of the Gate of Dawn' Vilnius", "Uploaded by", "GiW"]

Unbekannter Meister (genannt", "Meister des Kefermarkter Altars", "), um 1497.", "English:", "Nativity of Christ", "at the", "winged altar of the parish- and pilgrimage church Kefermarkt", ", Upper Austria. Anonymous master (called", "Master of the Kefermarkt Altarpiece", "), around 1497.", "Espa\u00f1ol:", "Natividad de Cristo", "en el retablo del", "altar alado de la iglesia parroquial y de peregrinaci\u00f3n de Kefermarkt", ", Alta Austria. Maestro an\u00f3nimo (conocido como el", "\"Maestro del retablo de Kefermarkt\"", "), alrededor de 1497.", "Polski:", "P\u0142askorze\u017aba", "Narodzenie Pa\u0144skie", "na\u00a0skrzydle", "o\u0142tarza szafiastego w\u00a0sanktuarium \u015bw.\u00a0Wolfganga", "w", "Kefermarkt", ", w", "G\u00f3rnej Austrii", ". Dzie\u0142o nieznanego mistrza powsta\u0142e oko\u0142o 1497 roku.", "\u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430:", "\u0420\u0456\u0437\u0434\u0432\u043e \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0435", "\u0437\u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u0440\u0438\u043b\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u0432\u0456\u0432\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0456 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0456\u044f\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u043b\u043e\u043c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u041a\u0435\u0444\u0435\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0440\u043a\u0442,", "\u0412\u0435\u0440\u0445\u043d\u044f \u0410\u0432\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0456\u044f", ", \u043d\u0435\u0432\u0456\u0434\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0439 \u0430\u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0431\u043b\u0438\u0437\u044c\u043a\u043e 1497 \u0440\u043e\u043a\u0443.", "\u010ce\u0161tina:", "D\u0159evo\u0159ezba", "Narozen\u00ed Krista", "z", "k\u0159\u00eddlov\u00e9ho olt\u00e1\u0159e", "v poutn\u00edm farn\u00edm kostele", "Sankt Wolfgang im Salzkammergut", ",", "Horn\u00ed Rakousy", ", od nezn\u00e1m\u00e9ho autora z doby kolem roku 1497.", "Magyar:", "Krisztus sz\u00fclet\u00e9se a kefermarkti pl\u00e9b\u00e1nia \u00e9s zar\u00e1ndoktemplom 1497 k\u00f6r\u00fcl k\u00e9sz\u00fclt sz\u00e1rnyas olt\u00e1r\u00e1n (", "Fels\u0151-Ausztria", ")", "\ud55c\uad6d\uc5b4:", "\uc0c1\uc624\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub9ac\uc544\uc5d0 \uc704\uce58\ud55c \uad50\uad6c \ubc0f \uc21c\ub840 \uad50\ud68c \ucf00\ud398\ub974\ub9c8\ub974\ud06c\ud2b8\uc758 \ub0a0\uac1c \ub2ec\ub9b0 \uc81c\ub2e8\uc5d0 \uc0c8\uaca8\uc9c4 '\uac15\ud0c4'(\uc608\uc218\uc758 \ud0c4\uc0dd). 1497\ub144\uacbd \uc775\uba85\uc758 \ub300\uac00\uc758 \uc791\ud488.", "Lietuvi\u0173:", "Kristaus gimimas", "parapijos altorius - ir piligrim\u0173 ba\u017eny\u010dia Kefermarkte", ", Auk\u0161tutin\u0117je Austrijoje. Autorius ne\u017einomas (", "Kefermarkto altoriaus autorius", "), apie 1497 m.", "\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438:", "\u0420\u043e\u0436\u0434\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0425\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043e", "\u2014 \u043a\u043e\u043f\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e \u0434\u0435\u043b\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u043e\u043b\u0442\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0442 \u0432\u043e", "\u0446\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u041a\u0435\u0444\u0435\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0440\u043a\u0442", ", \u0413\u043e\u0440\u043d\u0430 \u0410\u0432\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0458\u0430. \u041d\u0435\u043f\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0442 \u043c\u0430\u0458\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440, \u043e\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0443 1497 \u0433.", "Nederlands:", "De Geboorte van Christus", ", een", "altaarstuk", "uit circa 1497 in de kerk van", "Kefermarkt", "in", "Opper-Oostenrijk", "Portugu\u00eas:", "Nascimento de Jesus", "no", "ret\u00e1bulo", "do altar da igreja paroquial e de peregrina\u00e7\u00e3o de", "Kefermarkt", ",", "Alta \u00c1ustria", ".", "This media shows the protected monument with the number", "16512", "in Austria.", "(", "Commons", ",", "de", ",", "Wikidata", ")"]

filename: T'oros Roslin Gospels, Entry into Jerusalem, Walters Manuscript W.539, fol. 174r.jpg
author: ["\nWalters Art Museum Illuminated Manuscripts"]
description: ["English:", "This manuscript was made in 1262 by T\u2019oros Roslin, an extremely prominent illuminator, who extended the range of manuscript illuminations by introducing a whole cycle of images into the gospels rather than, as was traditional, only including the portraits of the evangelists. This particular manuscript was created at the scriptorium of Hromkla, which became the leading artistic center of Armenian Cilicia under the rule of catholicos Constantine I (1221-1267). As an extensive colophon starting on fol. 406v explains, T\u2019oros created this manuscript under commission from the nephew of Constantine, a priest also named T\u2019oros. It is one of seven known manuscripts bearing T\u2019oros Roslin\u2019s signature, and it is the most sumptuous of them all, with 15 miniatures and 67 smaller illustrations. The style of the images suggests that T\u2019oros had several assistants helping with the illustrations, though the overall quality remains extremely high. The manuscript was long cherished within the Armenian church. Even in the seventeenth century, its illumination served as a model for Armenian scribes, particularly Bargham and his son Mik\u2019ayel; see Jersualem, Armenian Patriarchate, no. 3438 and Washington DC, Freer Gallery, ms. 36.15; in the latter manuscript, Mik\u2019ayel explicitly refers to \u201cthe excellent scribe T\u2019oros, surnamed Roslin.\u201d"]

title: ["Folio 10 verso from a Book of Hours, The Trinity"]
description: ["This is a remarkably large and lavishly illuminated Book of Hours, combining French and English styles. The first leaf contains a list of obits members of the royal family and of the 4th, 5th, and 6th Earls of Ormond and their wives, so it was probably made for Anne Boleyn's grandfather, Thomas Butler (1426-1515), 7th Earl of Ormond, or a member of his family. It was given in the early 16th century to a chapel at 'Suthwyke', probably Southwick in Hampshire. The second of two miniatures of the Trinity shows the Three Persons, apparently naked except for a crown they share, 'clothed' by golden rays of heavenly light, and surrounded by angels and the symbols of the Four Evangelists."]

filename: Eagle nests at Memorial to fallen Airmen 141006-F-LX370-063.jpg
author: ["\nJustin Connaher"]
description: ["English:", "A rescued, disabled bald eagle lands on a perch at the Yukla 27 Memorial Park on Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, Alaska, Monday, Oct. 10, 2014. On Elmendorf Air Force Base, Sept. 22, 1995, a Boeing E-3B Sentry AWACS from the 962nd Airborne Air Control Squadron crashed shortly after takeoff for a routine surveillance training sortie.  Yukla 27 Memorial Park is dedicated in memory of the twenty-four American and Canadian airmen who lost their lives that morning.(U.S. Air Force photo/Justin Connaher)"]

filename: El Matriarcado - Santa Lucía de Tirajana.jpg
author: ["H. Zell"]
description:
["English:", "Sculpture "El Matriarcado" or "La Abuela y el nieto" ("The Matriarch" or "Grandmother and Granddaughter", 2011) by Victor Navarro Guedes (*1974, Spanish-Canarian sculptor from Santa Lucía de Tirajana).", "Inscription:", ""EL MATRIARCADO"", "CON ESTA ESCULTURA EL AYUNTAMIENTO DE SANTA LUCIA QUIERE RENDIR UN MERECIDO TRIBUTO A NUESTRAS ABUELAS, DEPOSITARIOS DE LA SABIDURÍA POPULAR Y CLAROS
REFERENTES DE NUESTRAS FAMILIAS. ESTE CONJUNTO ESCULTÓRICO SE INAUGURÓ EL DÍA 7 DE DICIEMBRE DE 2011, SIENDO ALCALDE - PRESIDENTE D. SILVERIO MATOS PÉREZ.
AUTOR
VICTOR NAVARRO GUEDES", ""THE MATRIARCH" With this sculpture the municipality of Santa Lucia wants to pay a fitting tribute to our
grandmothers, repositories of wisdom and important reference persons of our families. This sculpture was inaugurated on 7 December 2011, being Mayor - President D. Silverio Matos Pérez. 
Sculptor Victor Navarro Guedes", "Santa Lucía de Tirajana", ",", "Gran Canaria", ",", "Canary Islands", ",", "Spain", ".", "Deutsch:", "Sculptur "El Matriarcado" oder "La Abuela y el nieto" ("Die Matriarchin" or "Großmutter und Enkeltochter", 2011) von Victor Navarro Guedes (*1974, Spanisch-kanarischer Bildhauer aus Santa Lucía de Tirajana).", "Inschrift:", ""EL MATRIARCADO"", "CON ESTA ESCULTURA EL AYUNTAMIENTO DE SANTA LUCIA QUIERE RENDIR UN MERECIDO TRIBUTO A NUESTRAS ABUELAS, DEPOSITARIOS DE LA SABIDURÍA POPULAR Y CLAROS
REFERENTES DE NUESTRAS FAMILIAS. ESTE CONJUNTO ESCULTÓRICO SE INAUGURÓ EL DÍA 7 DE DICIEMBRE DE 2011, SIENDO ALCALDE - PRESIDENTE D. SILVERIO MATOS PÉREZ.
AUTOR
VICTOR NAVARRO GUEDES", ""DIE MATRIARCHIN" Mit dieser Skulptur will die Gemeinde Santa Lucia einen Tribut an unsere Großmütter zollen, Quellen der Weisheit und wichtige Bezugpersonen in unseren Familien. Diese Skulptur wurde am 7. Dezember eingeweiht 2011, ist Bürgermeister - Präsident D. Silvero Matos Perez", "Santa Lucía de Tirajana", ",", "Gran Canaria", ",", "Kanarische Inseln", ",", "Spanien", "."]

title: ["The Israelites Worship the Golden Calf and Moses Breaks the Tablets (Exodus 32:1-19)"]
description: ["English:", "This scene from Walters manuscript W.106 depicts a moment when the Israelites were in the desert after their escape from Egypt. Moses (shown here with horns, a sign of his encounter with divinity) had been on Mount Sinai, alone, receiving instructions from God. The Israelites strayed from faith in God in his absence"]
dimensions: ["height: 13.2 cm (5.1 in); width: 9.5 cm (3.7 in)", "dimensions QS:P2048,13.2U174728", "dimensions QS:P2049,9.5U174728"]

inscriptions: ["\n[Translation] When Moses went to the mountain to receive the Law, God said to him: 'Go down. Your people sin.' Moses descended and saw his people adoring a calf, which they made of gold and silver. When he saw this, he grew angry at them [and] hurled his tablets against the rock so that they broke; [Transliteration] Cum moyses fu al munt p[our] receivre la lei de[u] lu dit dece[n]de tun peple pecche. moysen d[e]se[n]d li vit sun peple aurer un veel q[u'i]l aveint fet d[']or e d[']argent. q[ua]nt ceo vit, li se corra, rua sa tables encuntre la roche q[u'i]l debruser[en]t."]

filename: La création dÈve (mosaïques de la Chapelle palatine, Palerme) (7026707189).jpg
author: ["Jean-Pierre Dalb\u00e9ra", "from Paris, France"]
description: ["La cr\u00e9ation d'\u00c8ve", "L'int\u00e9rieur de la chapelle est de style byzantin, il date de la fin de la d\u00e9cennie 1130, jusque dans les ann\u00e9es 1150-1160", "Au Xe si\u00e8cle, la Sicile est rattach\u00e9e au califat fatimide du Caire. L\u2019\u00eele  reste sous domination musulmane jusqu\u2019\u00e0 l\u2019arriv\u00e9e des Normands, qui, en 1059, obtiennent la souverainet\u00e9 des mains de la Papaut\u00e9  d\u00e9cid\u00e9e \u00e0 rechristianiser des territoires que Byzance n\u2019\u00e9tait plus capable de reconqu\u00e9rir.", "La conqu\u00eate normande s\u2019\u00e9chelonne entre 1060 \u00e0 1090. Finalement, en 1130, Roger II (1130-1154) obtient la couronne de l\u2019antipape Anaclet II (1130-1138) et rassemble les territoires normands en un royaume, choisissant naturellement Palerme comme capitale. Il y fait construire un palais et, dans celui-ci, un riche \u00e9difice cultuel, la Chapelle palatine, qui, par son architecture et son d\u00e9cor, demeure un exemple exceptionnel de m\u00e9tissage des arts chr\u00e9tiens d\u2019Orient et d\u2019Occident, et d\u2019art islamique.", "Article de Qantara sur la chapelle palatine", "www.qantara-med.org/qantara4/public/show_document.php?do_...", "Article de Wikipedia sur le palais des Rois Normands", "fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palais_des_Normands"]
source: ["La cr\u00e9ation d'\u00c8ve (mosa\u00efques de la Chapelle palatine, Palerme)"]

author: ["Anonymous", "Unknown author"]
description:
["English:", ""Wisdom hath builded her house" (Премудрость созда Себе дом), Novgorod (1548).", "The title of this type of icon is from Proverbs 9:1 and refers to the identification of Christ the Logos with Divine Wisdom (Hagia Sophia).", "The highly allegoric composition is centered on the "Feast of Wisdom" of Ephesians 3:8-12
The image of the "Power and Wisdom of GOD" on the throne is surrounded by the ranks of the heavenly hierarchy. 
The Theotokos sits on a throne with Christ Immanuel.
Divine Wisdom  is depicted in the depths of "divine darkness", dressed in white clothes, sitting on a golden throne with  a bowl in her left hand and a sceptre/staff in her right.  Her halo is formed from red and green rhombuses. Her throne is supported by seven pillars (Proverbs 9:1) and she is surrounded by the "first order of celestial entities" (", "De Coelesti Hierarchia", "7:4)
King Solomon is shown as the "servant of Wisdom", coming from the "hills of the City" to the Theotokos with Immanuel (Proverbs 9:3).", "An early icon of the "Wisdom has builded her house" type is a 14th-century fresco  in the Church of the Assumption in Volotovo Field, Veliky Novgorod.", "[1]", "This icon has some parallels with the Volotovo fresco, including the diagonal table and the shape of the temple, the slaughter of two calves, King Solomon approaching with an unrolled scroll, and the  figure of  hymnographer Kozma Maiumsky.", "icon-art.info", "icons.pstgu.ru", "Русский:", ""Премудрость созда Себе дом". 1548 г. Новгород.", "Первая половина XVI века. Новгород
Дерево, темпера. 146 × 106
Происходит из собора Афанасия и Кирилла Александрийских Кириллова монастыря близ Новгорода", "ГТГ, инв. 28830"]

filename: Saint Sophia The Wisdom of God - Google Art Project.jpg
artist: ["English:", "Unknown"]
title: ["English:", "Saint Sophia The Wisdom of God"]
description: ["English:", "In the center there is a figure of Our Lady of the Sign, standing on the crescent-shaped moon. She is portrayed in rotunda, supported by seven pillars. Wisdom, or Sophia, symbolizes the son of God, about whom it is said in the Parables of Solomon: \u201cWisdom has built her house; she has set up its seven pillars\u201d. These words are written on the cornice of rotunda. These words refer to Jesus Christ, the Son of God, who is called \"God's Wisdom\" in Epistles. The word \u201cHouse\u201d refers to the Virgin Mary, who gave birth to the Son of God.", "God the Father is portrayed above the rotunda, from whom the Holy Spirit descends down the Virgin Mary in the form of the dove. \nSeven Archangels are depicted on both sides of God the Father, holding the signs of their ministry: to the right \u2013 Michael with a sword, Uriel with a lightning, Raphael with alabastron of chrism, to the left \u2013 Gabriel with a lily, Salathiel with beads, Jegudiel with a royal crown and  Barachiel with flowers on a white shawl.", "On seven steps of ambon that symbolizes the Church of God on earth, in front of the Virgin Mary there stand forefathers and prophets, who announced the advent of Wisdom to the world: to the right: Moses with the tablets, Aaron with a rod, David with the Ark of the Covenant, to the left - Isaiah with the Charter of his prophecy, Jeremiah with a scroll, Ezekiel with gates shut and Daniel with a corner stone. Seven Virtues are indicated on the steps: Faith, Hope, Love, Purity, Humility, Grace, Glory."]
collection: ["\nSt. Sophia of Kyiv"]
source/photographer: ["RQG3jtzF4ZL4Nw at Google Cultural Institute", ", zoom level maximum"]

author: ["\nRijksmuseum"]
description: ["Nederlands:", "Identificatie", "Titel(s):", "Christus en de rijke jongeman", "Objecttype:", "prent boekillustratie", "Objectnummer:", "RP-P-1961-729", "Opschriften / Merken:", "verzamelaarsmerk, verso midden, gestempeld: Lugt 2228a", "Omschrijving:", "Christus en twee discipelen tegenover rijke jongeman met muts in hand.", "Vervaardiging", "Vervaardiger:", "prentmaker: Meester van Antwerpen (I) (toegeschreven aan)", "Plaats vervaardiging:", "Nederlanden", "Datering:", "1485 - 1491", "Fysieke kenmerken:", "houtsnede, handgekleurd in paars, rood, oranje, geel, groen, bruin en grijs", "Materiaal:", "papier", "Techniek:", "houtsnede / met de hand kleuren", "Afmetingen:", "beeld: h 95 mm \u00d7 b 130 mm", "Toelichting", "E\u00e9n van 46 houtsnedes uit Ludolphus de Saxonia \"Tboeck vandan leven ons heeren Jesu Christi\", een anonieme Nederlandse vertaling. Deze versie van het werk van Ludolphus bevat houtsneden van de Meester van Gouda (II), de Meester van Antwerpen (I) en de Meester van Haarlem. Botke, K. Boek van Ludolphus is voor het eerst uitgegeven in 1487 door Geeraert Leeu te Antwerpen. In 1488 uitgegeven door Claes Leeu te Antwerpen, in 1495 en 1499 en 1519 door Peter van Os te Zwolle en in 1510 door A. van Berghen te Antwerpen. Deze 46 houtsneden komen waarschijnlijk uit een uitgave van Peter van Os. Botke, K.", "Onderwerp", "Wat:", "Christ urges a rich young man (a certain ruler), who is kneeling before him, to seek perfection (Matthew 19:16-22; Mark 10:17-22; Luke 18:18-23)", "Verwerving en rechten", "Verwerving:", "overdracht van beheer 1961", "Copyright:", "Publiek domein"]

filename: Leaf from the Morgan Picture Bible - Google Art Project.jpg
artist: ["Unknown  \u2013 illuminator"]
title: ["Leaf from the Morgan Picture Bible", "title QS:P1476,en:\"Leaf from the Morgan Picture Bible\"", "label QS:Len,\"Leaf from the Morgan Picture Bible\""]
description: ["The reverse side of the Morgan Picture Bible leaf continues the story of David and his rebellious son Absalom. On the upper left, the armies of David and Absalom meet in a fierce battle. Horses and knights overlap each other in the confusion of combat, with the knights raising their weapons above their heads, ready to strike. In the next scene to the right, Absalom's hair catches on the branches of a tree as his mule passes under it. Taking advantage of the situation, David's servants pierce the helpless Absalom with their spears. In the scene below, David anxiously awaits news of the battle, his eyes directed up at a servant, who points to the approaching riders, and at the scene of his son's death above. His pained expression and upraised hand seem to indicate that he expects unwelcome news.", "An architectural structure and variation in the background color give structure to the miniature's various scenes, echoing the forms and colors of contemporary stained-glass windows."]
medium: ["\n\"Tempera colors, gold leaf, and ink on parchment\""]

filename: Initial V- The Descent of the Holy Spirit - Google Art Project.jpg
artist: ["Unknown  \u2013 illuminator"]
title: ["Initial V: The Descent of the Holy Spirit", "title QS:P1476,en:\"Initial V: The Descent of the Holy Spirit\"", "label QS:Len,\"Initial V: The Descent of the Holy Spirit\""]
description: ["The Holy Spirit, in the form of a dove, descends from the arc of heaven into an illuminated initial V. The initial introduces the hymn sung at Vespers (the evening prayer service) on Pentacost Sunday. Pentecost commemorates the descent of the Holy Spirit on the disciples, which occurred after the death, Resurrection, and Ascension of Christ, and marks the beginning of the Christian Church's mission to the world. The frenzied activity within the initial is particularly appropriate to Pentecost, which the Bible describes as \"a sound of heaven, as of a mighty wind coming\" that suddenly descended on the apostles, who then simultaneously preached in a variety of languages to a great crowd of people."]
medium: ["\n\"Tempera colors, gold leaf, gold paint, and ink on parchment\""]
dimensions: ["height: 192 mm (7.55 in); width: 132 mm (5.19 in)", "dimensions QS:P2048,192U174789", "dimensions QS:P2049,132U174789"]
notes: ["More info at museum site"]

description: ["In Ethiopian Christian Orthodox churches, religious images are usually covered with cloth between services.", "The fabric selected for this purpose is often gauzy and delicately beautiful, as is the case here.  I especially love the spray of flowers in jewel-tone colors that adorns the fabric.", "This image of the Virgin Mary and the Infant Jesus is relatively new; it is dated 1991 in the lower right.", "Church of Bet Medhane Alem, Lalibela, Ethiopia."]

filename: Walters Ms. W917 - Apocalypse by Andrew of Caesarea f.201v New Jerusalem as a bride.jpg
author: ["\nanonymous Russian Old Believer"]
description: ["English:", "Walters Ms. W917 - Apocalypse with commentaries by Andrew of Caesarea This manuscript was made around 1800 by the \u201cOld Believers,\u201d a group of Russian Christians who dissented from the Russian Orthodox Church and were subsequently persecuted and excommunicated. Because their books were often confiscated and they were forbidden to use printing presses, they continued to write important works such as this one by hand. The manuscript contains the text of the New Testament book of Revelation along with a patristic commentary, which is accompanied by a series of seventy-one striking full-page miniatures."]

filename: BnF MS Gr510 folio 440 recto - detail - Helena and the Invention of the True Cross.jpg
author: ["\nBiblioth\u00e8que nationale de France"]
description: ["English:", "Portrait of the empress Helena and her Invention of the True Cross in a 9th century Byzantine manuscript.", "Saint Helena, mother of Constantine the Great, was made Augusta by her son. According to Christian tradition, she made a pilgrimage to the Holy Land and discovered in Jerusalem the original wooden crosses on which Jesus and the two thieves were crucified. The", "inventio", "(invention, discovery) of the True Cross was a popular subject in mediaeval legend.", "Detail from a Greek manuscript dated 879-883 AD and containing the homilies of Gregory of Nazianzus, now in the National Library of France.", "(BnF MS Gr510 folio 440 recto - detail)"]
source: ["Illustrated painted parchment Greek manuscript (879-883 AD) of the homilies of Gregory of Nazianzus in the Biblioth\u00e8que nationale de France.\n(BnF MS grec 510) folio 440r.", "https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/btv1b84522082/f891"]

filename: Russian - Great Deesis with Prophets - Walters 37625.jpg
artist: ["Anonymous", "(", "Russia", ")", "Unknown author"]
title: ["Great Deesis with Prophets"]
description: ["English:", "These panels reproduce the upper two tiers of the screen (known as the iconostasis) that separates the nave from the altar in Orthodox churches. Such sets, of which this is one of the earliest known, were used by priests for makeshift altars and by lay people for personal prayer. In the upper row, the Virgin and Child are surrounded by Old Testament prophets who hold scrolls with passages foretelling Christ's birth: Habakkuk (?), Micah, Jeremiah, Moses, Daniel, David, Solomon, Jonah, Jacob, Isaiah (?), Gedeon, and Zechariah. Below, the adult Christ is seated on the throne of judgment, flanked by holy persons who entreat him to forgive our sins. On his right are the Virgin, St. Peter, Metropolitan Peter of Moscow, St. Sergius of Radonezh (a famous Russian hermit), and St. George. On his left stand John the Baptist, St. Paul, Metropolitan Alexis of Moscow, St. Cyril of Belozersk (another renowned Russian monk), and St. Demetrius."]

filename: Brooklyn Museum 76.132 Painted Icon Double Triptych (3).jpg
artist: ["Unknown author", "Unknown author"]
title: ["English:", "Painted Icon, Double Triptych"]
description: ["English:", "Side A: Virgin and child in central panel flanked on either side by scenes of Crucifixion.  Ascension of Christ, St. George and the dragon, and figures representing possibly the servants of St. George.  There are inscriptions over the heads of some figures.  Colors are mainly blue, yellow, red, and green.  Side B: Central panel is scene of Christ in majesty with radiating nimbus surrounded by sleeping figures and on side panels figures of Ethiopian saints, scene of the raising of Lazarus (possibly), a shepard and an Ethiopian King. Colors are mainly yellow, red and blue.  Condition: All painted surfaces in need of stabilization.  Condition is fragile.  Linen worn especially at edges.", "English:", "The Ethiopian church's strong link to Eastern Orthodox Christianity can be seen in the use of icons. The figures are motionless in posture as in Byzantine art, but they have Ethiopian features.    One central panel of this icon shows the Virgin and Child flanked by the archangels Gabriel and Michael. The left panel depicts Saint George slaying the dragon, above, and Takla Haymonat and Ewostatewas, two local saints, below. On the right panel, the Resurrection is represented as Christ releasing Adam and Eve from Limbo.    The opposite central panel portrays Christ wearing a crown of thorns and being mocked before Pontius Pilate. Below are the husband and wife who commissioned the icon. The upper part of the panel on the right shows a local saint, Abo, with a dove and pairs of lions and leopards. The lower part depicts the entombment of Christ."]

author: ["A. Davey", "from Where I Live Now: Pacific Northwest"]
description: ["In the new Church of St. Mary of Zion, Axum, Ethiopia.", "I was captivated by the way the backlighting added to the image's inherent drama and mystery.", "I also liked the contrast between the realistic depiction of Christ in the center of the image, with its limited palette of colors, and the stylized polychrome figure on the traditional piece in the lower corner.", "Please see skibriye's comment below for an interesting and well-written explanation of this image and its importance to Ethiopian Orthodox Christians."]

description: ["English:", "British Museum image: Royal 2 B VII f. 168v. description: ["English:", "This is a view of the fountain located within the site of the South Tower of the World Trade Center, which was destroyed on September 11, 2001.
